    "bespokeVisualization": "The old browser-login loop visibly tangles while the App Store Connect key takes a straight path to certificates and profiles.",
    "heroJourney": {
      "identity": "Codename One is introduced as the Java native-app platform and the topic is iOS signing.",
      "problem": "Certificate setup depends on automating a human login experience that changes independently of the build tool.",
      "difficulty": "Passwords, two-factor prompts, page changes, bundle IDs, certificates, profiles, devices, and push setup create a fragile chain.",
      "intervention": "A revocable App Store Connect API key gives the standalone wizard a supported machine-to-machine path.",
      "victory": "The developer launches one project-bound command and auto-setup creates or reuses the signing assets the build needs."
    },
